Here&rsquo;s a creative idea I&rsquo;d never considered before. I&rsquo;ve written code like this, but accidentally, and then it looks wrong so I change it back. Here&rsquo;s a quick example:
if ( 42 == myInt ) as opposed to if ( myInt == 42 )
The former may be better to use because occasionally we all forget to put that second &ldquo;=&rdquo; in there, and we accidentally turn our comparison operator into an assignment operator.
